eveloped frameworks that are crucial for research on oral poetics, such as construction grammar or conversation analysis. The key for connecting the two disciplines is their common focus on usage and performance. This collection of papers explores how some of the latest research on language and cognition can contribute to advances in oral studies. At the same time, it shows how research on verbal art in its natural, oral medium can lead to new insights in semantics, pragmatics, or multimodal communication. The ultimate goal is to pave the way towards a Cognitive Oral Poetics, a new interdisciplinary field for the study or oral poetry as a window to the mind.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aCognitive grammar. 0aElectronic books. 0aFolk poetryxHistory and criticism. 0aOral-formulaic analysis. 0aPoetics. 4aOral formulaic style. 4aconversation analysis. 4aframes and constructions. 4amultimodality and narrative structuring. 70(DE-601)1048205860(DE-588)4246269-1aKognitive Linguistik2gnd 70(DE-601)1056914370(DE-588)4131940-0aMündliche Literatur2gnd 70(DE-601)1061979590(DE-588)4046449-0aPoetik2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAntovic, Mihailo, eeditor.1 aPagán Cánovas, Cristóbal, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831103846800 cprintz978311034838540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110348538423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110348538.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SS